\begin{align*}
\frac{x-3}{16} &= \frac{8}{x} + 3\\
\implies \frac{x^2-3x}{16} &= \frac{8 + 3x}{x}\\
\implies x^2-3x &= 128 + 48x\\
\therefore x^2-51x-128 &= 0\\
\therefore x &= \frac{51\pm\sqrt{3601}}{2}
\end{align*}

Therefore, the sum of all $x$ that satisfy the given equation is $\boxed{51}$. </answer>

